<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="40" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="40">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="40">
<bibRefCitation author="d'Orbigny, A" journalOrPublisher="Magasin de Zoologie" pageId="49" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 44" refId="B61" refString="d'Orbigny, A, 1835. Synopsis terrestrium et fluviatilium molluscorum, in suo per Americam meriodionalem itinere. Magasin de Zoologie 5 (61): 1 - 44" title="Synopsis terrestrium et fluviatilium molluscorum, in suo per Americam meriodionalem itinere." volume="5" year="1835">
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’Orbigny">d'Orbigny</normalizedToken>
(1835)
</bibRefCitation>
did not state on how many specimens his description was based; he said his taxon was identical to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bowdich" authorityYear="1822" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Helix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Helix regina" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="23" pageNumber="40" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="regina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="40">Helix regina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="β">β</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Férussac">Ferussac</normalizedToken>
, 1821. In 
<bibRefCitation author="d'Orbigny, A" journalOrPublisher="P. Bertrand, Paris" pageId="49" pageNumber="66" refId="B60" refString="d'Orbigny, A, 1834-1847. Voyage dans l'Amerique meriodionale (le Bresil, la republique orientale de l'Uruguay, la republique Argentine, la Patagonie, la republique du Chile, la republique de Bolivia, la republique du Perou), execute pendant les annees 1826, 1827, 1828, 1829, 1830, 1831, 1832, et 1833. Tome 5, Partie 3, Mollusques. P. Bertrand, Paris" title="Voyage dans l'Amerique meriodionale (le Bresil, la republique orientale de l'Uruguay, la republique Argentine, la Patagonie, la republique du Chile, la republique de Bolivia, la republique du Perou), execute pendant les annees 1826, 1827, 1828, 1829, 1830, 1831, 1832, et 1833. Tome 5, Partie 3, Mollusques" year="1834 - 1847">
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’Orbigny">d'Orbigny</normalizedToken>
(1838 [1834-1847]
</bibRefCitation>
: 260) the locality was specified as &quot;environs des Missions de San-Xavier et de Concepcion&quot;; see 
<bibRefCitation author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="Basteria" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="113 - 135" refId="B6" refString="Breure, ASH, 1973. Index to the neotropical land Mollusca described by Alcide d'Orbigny, with notes on the localities of the mainland species. Basteria 37: 113 - 135" title="Index to the neotropical land Mollusca described by Alcide d'Orbigny, with notes on the localities of the mainland species." volume="37" year="1973">Breure 1973</bibRefCitation>
. Of the material found, none of the shells corresponds exactly with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’Orbigny’s">d'Orbigny's</normalizedToken>
figure. The current systematic position is according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Richardson, CL" journalOrPublisher="Tryonia" pageId="51" pageNumber="68" pagination="1 - 164" refId="B113" refString="Richardson, CL, 1993. Bulimulacea: catalog of species. Amphibulimidae, Anadromidae, Grangerellidae, Odontostomidae, Orthalicidae. Tryonia 27: 1 - 164" title="Bulimulacea: catalog of species. Amphibulimidae, Anadromidae, Grangerellidae, Odontostomidae, Orthalicidae." volume="27" year="1993">Richardson (1993</bibRefCitation>
: 108).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
